---
---

<section id="work" style="border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07); background:#0a0a0b;">
  <div style="max-width:1120px; margin:0 auto; padding:104px 32px;" class="section-pad">
    <div
      data-reveal
      style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace; font-size:12px; letter-spacing:0.14em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#6f6f6f; margin-bottom:10px;"
    >
      How it works
    </div>
    <h2
      data-reveal
      style="font-weight:600; font-size:38px; line-height:1.12; letter-spacing:-0.025em; margin:0 0 14px; color:#fafafa;"
    >
      Two ways to work together.
    </h2>
    <p
      data-reveal
      style="font-size:17px; line-height:1.6; color:#9a9a9a; max-width:560px; margin:0 0 48px;"
    >
      Most teams start with a Launch Engagement to stand the function up, then keep it running on a
      retainer. Pick the one that fits where you are.
    </p>

    <div class="offerings-grid" style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:24px;">
      <!-- Tier 1: Launch Engagement -->
      <div data-reveal class="tier-card">
        <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; margin-bottom:20px; gap:12px; flex-wrap:wrap;">
          <span
            style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace; font-size:11px; letter-spacing:0.1em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--accent); background:color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 12%, transparent); border:1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 28%, transparent); padding:5px 10px; border-radius:6px;"
          >
            Primary · start here
          </span>
          <span style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace; font-size:12.5px; color:#8b8b8b;">
            8-week minimum
          </span>
        </div>

        <h3 style="font-weight:600; font-size:25px; letter-spacing:-0.02em; margin:0 0 8px; color:#fafafa;">
          Launch Engagement
        </h3>
        <p style="font-size:15px; line-height:1.6; color:#9a9a9a; margin:0 0 24px;">
          A fixed, focused sprint that stands up a real, working developer relations function
          instead of just rewriting your docs.
        </p>

        <div style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace; font-size:11.5px; letter-spacing:0.08em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#6f6f6f; margin-bottom:14px;">
          Best if
        </div>
        <p style="font-size:14.5px; line-height:1.6; color:#c4c4c4; margin:0 0 24px;">
          You're launching or relaunching a developer product and no one owns the developer
          experience yet.
        </p>

        <div style="height:1px; background:rgba(255,255,255,0.08); margin:0 0 22px;"></div>

        <div style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace; font-size:11.5px; letter-spacing:0.08em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#6f6f6f; margin-bottom:16px;">
          What you get
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:12px; margin-bottom:30px;">
          <div style="display:flex; gap:12px; align-items:flex-start; font-size:15px; color:#d2d2d2;">
            <span style="color:var(--accent); flex:none;">✓</span>
            Discovery with your real users &amp; support channels
          </div>
          <div style="display:flex; gap:12px; align-items:flex-start; font-size:15px; color:#d2d2d2;">
            <span style="color:var(--accent); flex:none;">✓</span>
            A content &amp; community plan tied to actual gaps
          </div>
          <div style="display:flex; gap:12px; align-items:flex-start; font-size:15px; color:#d2d2d2;">
            <span style="color:var(--accent); flex:none;">✓</span>
            Published articles / videos and priority docs fixes
          </div>
          <div style="display:flex; gap:12px; align-items:flex-start; font-size:15px; color:#d2d2d2;">
            <span style="color:var(--accent); flex:none;">✓</span>
            A live community space and a first AMA / office hours
          </div>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-top:auto; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; gap:16px; padding-top:6px;">
          <span style="font-size:14px; color:#8b8b8b;">Custom scope, sized to your team</span>
          <a href="#contact" class="tier-cta-primary">Start here →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Tier 2: Ongoing Retainer -->
      <div data-reveal class="tier-card">
        <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; margin-bottom:20px; gap:12px; flex-wrap:wrap;">
          <span
            style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace; font-size:11px; letter-spacing:0.1em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#9a9a9a; background:rgba(255,255,255,0.05); border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.10); padding:5px 10px; border-radius:6px;"
          >
            Primary · ongoing
          </span>
          <span style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace; font-size:12.5px; color:#8b8b8b;">
            monthly
          </span>
        </div>

        <h3 style="font-weight:600; font-size:25px; letter-spacing:-0.02em; margin:0 0 8px; color:#fafafa;">
          Ongoing DevRel Retainer
        </h3>
        <p style="font-size:15px; line-height:1.6; color:#9a9a9a; margin:0 0 24px;">
          The function, kept alive and growing: content, community, and a steady presence for your
          developers.
        </p>

        <div style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace; font-size:11.5px; letter-spacing:0.08em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#6f6f6f; margin-bottom:14px;">
          Best if
        </div>
        <p style="font-size:14.5px; line-height:1.6; color:#c4c4c4; margin:0 0 24px;">
          You've built momentum and need someone consistent to sustain it rather than a one-off push.
        </p>

        <div style="height:1px; background:rgba(255,255,255,0.08); margin:0 0 22px;"></div>

        <div style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace; font-size:11.5px; letter-spacing:0.08em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#6f6f6f; margin-bottom:16px;">
          What you get
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:12px; margin-bottom:30px;">
          <div style="display:flex; gap:12px; align-items:flex-start; font-size:15px; color:#d2d2d2;">
            <span style="color:var(--accent); flex:none;">✓</span>
            Continuous content production
          </div>
          <div style="display:flex; gap:12px; align-items:flex-start; font-size:15px; color:#d2d2d2;">
            <span style="color:var(--accent); flex:none;">✓</span>
            Active community management
          </div>
          <div style="display:flex; gap:12px; align-items:flex-start; font-size:15px; color:#d2d2d2;">
            <span style="color:var(--accent); flex:none;">✓</span>
            A regular point of contact for your developer audience
          </div>
          <div style="display:flex; gap:12px; align-items:flex-start; font-size:15px; color:#d2d2d2;">
            <span style="color:var(--accent); flex:none;">✓</span>
            Optional event representation &amp; office hours
          </div>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-top:auto; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; gap:16px; padding-top:6px;">
          <span style="font-size:14px; color:#8b8b8b;">Monthly · after a Launch Engagement</span>
          <a href="#contact" class="tier-cta-secondary">Let's talk →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
